<section id="command-pencolor">
<title>PENCOLOR</title>
<indexterm><primary>PENCOLOR</primary></indexterm>
<indexterm><primary>PC</primary></indexterm>

<variablelist>

<varlistentry><term>Synopsis</term>
<listitem>
<synopsis><command>PENCOLOR</command>
<command>PENCOLOUR</command>
<command>PC</command></synopsis>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>Description</term>
<listitem>
<para>
Outputs pen color information.
This is either a color index (a number from 0 - 15), or a list containing [red green blue] intensities, depending on how the pen color was set.
</para>

</listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term>Example</term>
<listitem>
<programlisting><userinput>SETPENCOLOR [100 200 50]
SHOW PENCOLOR</userinput>
[100 200 50]</programlisting>

<programlisting><userinput>SETPENCOLOR 2
SHOW PENCOLOR</userinput>
2</programlisting>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
</variablelist>

</section>
